description:
&lt;p&gt;Principal Clinical Psychologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An extremely exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a highly motivated and committed individual to be the psychology lead for the Fylde Coast Urgent Care Pathway. The UCP comprises of the Adult Crisis, Home Treatment Team and Mental Health Liaison Team. These fast paced and high risk teams offer a magnitude of exciting development opportunities for the successful candidate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These large teams covering a complex locality work best as an MDT to optimise patient care, the successful candidate will be an integral part of this MDT and offer a supportive and mentoring role to the 8a Psychologist within HTT (vacant post). This new role will also see the introduction of a psychologist into the Mental Health Liaison Team and an opportunity to enhance an already robust and extremely skilled service by offering formulations, support, advice and training to one of the most front facing teams of Mental Health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An enhanced DBS check is required for this post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Christiaan Morgan to discuss this exciting opportunity in more detail on: 07969 478413 or .christiaan.morgan@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
